\begin_layout Plain Layout

Raw signals ($D$) are first processed ($D'$) and split into $m$ segments
 ($W_i$) from which feature vectors ($X_i$) are extracted.
 Given features ($X_i$), a model with parameters $
\backslash
theta$ scores $c$ activity classes $Y_i = 
\backslash
{y^1, 
\backslash
ldots, y^c
\backslash
}$ with a confidence vector $p_i$.
 
\end_layout

